"title": "5886: individualism",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5886",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The recognition of individuality, of the differences between particular people, and of their special gifts, needs and character. In a negative sense, the term can mean placing the needs of individuals above those of the church as a whole, which is contrary to the biblical emphasis on all believers sharing in the common ministry of the body of Christ.</p>\n<h2>Individualism stresses the differences between people</h2>\n<h3>Recognising people's special gifts</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:4-1Cor12:6\">1CO 12:4–12:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:6-Rom12:8\">ROM 12:6–12:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:8-1Cor12:11\">1CO 12:8–12:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:28-1Cor12:30\">1CO 12:28–12:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:11\">EPH 4:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:4\">HEB 2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:10\">1PE 4:10</a></p>\n<h3>Recognising people's abilities and opportunities</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:14-Matt25:15\">MAT 25:14–25:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:12-Luke19:13\">LUK 19:12–19:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:7\">1CO 4:7</a></p>\n<h2>Individualism and the church</h2>\n<h3>Recognising the parts people play in the church, the body of Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:12\">1CO 12:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:4-Rom12:5\">ROM 12:4–12:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:14\">1CO 12:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:17-1Cor12:20\">1CO 12:17–12:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:27\">1CO 12:27</a></p>\n<h3>Individualism must not emphasise the individual at the expense of the church as a whole</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:21-1Cor12:26\">1CO 12:21–12:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:3\">ROM 12:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:10\">ROM 12:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:16\">ROM 12:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:3\">PHP 2:3</a></p>\n<h3>Contrary to self-seeking individualism, believers should share in the common ministry of the body of Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:42\">ACT 2:42</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:44\">ACT 2:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:34-Acts4:35\">ACT 4:34–4:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:13-2Cor8:14\">2CO 8:13–8:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor9:13\">2CO 9:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:16\">HEB 13:16</a></p>",
